-- Slovakia Plans to Reduce Subsidies for Solar Power, Hospodarske Reports
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2010-10-27T05:17:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/slovakia-plans-to-reduce-subsidies-for-solar-power-hospodarske-reports.html
The Slovak government will copy its
Czech counterpart in slashing subsidies for solar power
producers, Hospodarske noviny reported, citing Slovak Economy
Ministry official Martin Chren.  Slovak Economy Minister Juraj Misko introduced a draft of
law that would allow support only for solar power plants with a
capacity of maximum 100 kilowatt hours, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  